body:
### Description

In the last days i was trying to understand why suddenly vtsls and other LSPs like eslint and biome stopped working.

But I would not get any log in `.local/state/nvim/lsp.log` nor any `:message` in neovim.

Suddenly, adding `version = "*"` in  which pointed lspconfig to v2.5.0 started working again.

I'm not sure how i could extract more info for understanding why it may happen.

Is some change needed for nightly?

**INFO:**

`lazy.nvim` as package manager with `version = false`

```
NVIM v0.12.0-dev-1673+g7be031f397
Build type: RelWithDebInfo
LuaJIT 2.1.1763318511
Run "nvim -V1 -v" for more info
```

nvim-lspconfig commit e0fae251f8459940331960106d4bd9457cec23de on master


